M a l e: Protarsomeres 1 to 3 distinctly widened. Aedeagus (
Figs 70, 71
) 0.32 mm long, symmetrical, fairly sclerotized. Articular processes large, prominent. Apical process of median lobe fairly long, inflexed, tapering, with acute tip. Parameres in lateral view oblique, almost evenly wide posterior bases, in dorsal view narrowed posterior mid-length, weakly curved and evenly narrow in apical third. Internal sac tubular, lacking sclerites, without flagellum.
